Columba v1.0 

Bug fixes:
- TreeSelection after Popup fixed. The problem was that the boolean flags to check
  if this event is popup-event must be reset to false after the menu is shown.
- Refactored MarkAsReadTimer. It is now independant of the TableController which 
  makes more sense. It works with the util Timer to avoid execting an add to 
  the CommandProcess in the EventDispatcherThread. It fixes unwanted MarkAsRead 
  when the messagepreview is hidden.
- #958065 sort order, when changing columns. ColumnHeaderTable model should be 
  listener to tablecolumnmodel
- Small bug in synchronization of HeaderLists: Deleted local uids were not 
  counted in the message balance. This resulted in a complete sync which is 
  not necessary.
- Minor IMAP tweaks to get more performance/nicer connection handling.
- Flags and Attributes need to be cloned when used as parameters in the 
  addMessage method.
- Headerlist was not instantiated when new subfolders were created.
- Virtual Folder now also does binning on innerCopy and MarkMessage. Huge
  speedup for large copy/move/delete commands on VirtualFolders.
- All IMAPFolders can now be synced by the checkmail action.
- #1281648, edit in external editor doesn't work
- #1281632, edit group dialog doesn't let you add new contacts
- use interfaces for selection handling where possible, improved package 
  dependencies 
- cleanup of gui.toolbar package, resembling the extendable menu code
- #1276646, Selection in Copy Messag Dialog
- #1275847 Mark as read after N seconds has no effect. Issues fixed.
- Default Account should be seleted in the Composer instead of the first account.
- Charset Menu fixes. There are not as many charsets available as 
  previously assumed.
- Do decoding of message body streams
- Handle too long Strings when writing headercache.
- Refactoring of the HeaderCacheFramework. Now HeaderList and its persistance 
  are transparently handled. Now we can even start looking into using
  BerkelyDB in the future. Unplanned (but not unwelcome), this refactoring
  also includes some IMAP speedups :-)
- make sure that message list and message viewer are cleared, if no 
  folder or message selected
- fixed composer layout, component height should be the same in every row
- replace all AbstractFolder class references with interface IMailFolder
- Speedup of MessageViewing: Use a static instance of DateTimeFormater 
  instead of reinstantiating every time.
- when changing folder selections, sometimes the row selection was set, 
  but wasn't visible. In this case, the scrollpane wasn't changed correctly
- folder options were executed twice, when selecting folder
- JTextComponent undo/redo works correctly again
- signature viewer uses same message viewer-like box style now, added 
  "edit signature..." button, now visually more separated from text editor.
- fixed table cellrenderer, selection foreground/background color
- #1256120 Save as Draft should not append signature. 
- refactored chat example plugin to remove cyclic dependencies, 
  added api/ source folder (first test of using multiple source folders in a plugin) - works perfectly ;-)
- removed all cyclic dependencies from core (columba) package
- #1250862, add menuitem to view the error log file
- #1250951, wrong font color in message list component (still, 
  the extension interface is too complicated, going to simplify later)
- fixed pending resource loader problem. This works now correctly. 
  See chat.altura plugin for examples on how to load resources. 
  "this.getClass().getResourceAsStream(String str)" does the trick.
- fine-tune default theme settings
- updated winlaf look and feel (jdic project containing bugfixes to make 
  the JDK win L&F look more native)
- Added native support for Mac application and web browser open.
- added new recipient list autocomplete textfield
- Performance tuned mbox importer.
- Add a default signature when creating a new account.
- Messages are marked as deleted before moved to trash. Now Expunge 
  Folders works as users expect it to on the trash folder.
- Handle multiparts in the alternative part. Ignore charset of HMTLDocument.
- refactored plugin system, refactored menu extension system
- Refactoring and clean-up for platfrom independence. From this commit 
  on, all not natively supported platforms are again supported.
  I have created default fallbacks for the mime association and the trayicon
  features. It is now also easier to integrate the mac features with their native jars.
- Html to Text was not charset aware.
- Image Viewer speedup: Use the FAST scaling method instead of smooth.
- Added a new edit Signature action. This opens the external text editor 
  to edit the Signature. Can be run from Identitypanel or Composer. I also
  added the MailAccount configuration to the Composer menu.
- Virtual Folder speedup: Packed searches instead of every single for its 
  own. Also fixed some problems with recursive VFolders.
- selection handling changed. If you open the context-menu, the selection 
  changes will not trigger the message viewer. This works for the tree and 
  the message list.
- #958067,cut/copy/paste messages throws exception fixed
- Added more information on the messageFlagedChanged event. With this
  additional information it is now possible to update the VFolders 
  correctly if the flags change. Further, a new search is triggered if the 
  flags change so that the VFolders get these changes. There is still a good 
  way missing for removing messages after a Flag change.
	

Columba v1.0 RC3

New features:
- vFolders are now active and reflect changes of the folders
- cleanup of message viewer component
- added show attachments inline viewer for message viewer
- added plugin-based viewers for various contents types
- cleanup of table model for message list component
- new filter toolbar for message list
- moved concept of folders, filters and filter actions into core 
- improved plugin system exception handling 
- improved interpreter plugin support 
- new Groovy (http://groovy.codehaus.org/) interpreter plugin, allows
  you to write plugins in the Groovy language 
- added a Groovy language Hello World plugin 
- cleanup of header-cache, performance improvements 
- cleanup of SpamAssassin plugin, added filter action
- integration of JDIC (https://jdic.dev.java.net/) for trayicon support
  and opening attachments with the system's default application 
- sending messages can now be canceled
- more progress updates on IMAP operations
- updated to JGoodies Looks 1.3.1
- updated to JGoodes Forms 1.0.5
- updated berkleydb je to version 1.7.1
- cleanup of Filter Editing Dialog
- Added more exception handling to the pop3 header cache. Should help 
  in debugging any further errors. (tstich)

  
